				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\bar B$\end{document} (defined as the total magnetic flux divided by the AR surface area), reached the highest level (188 Mx cmâ2) by the 4th day of the AR evolution and decreased steadily after that in spite of the ensuing episodes of flux emergence (Figure 19, lower panel).
