Interpreting the power laws found for emission from the chromosphere, the best model to be compatible with the power-law exponents found was that by Solanki et al. (1991) (see Figure 32). However, the emission from the chromosphere is not simply linked to the energy deposited in the region where an emission line is formed, as radiation from the photosphere and neighbouring chromospheric layers also contribute.
